<br>
Fumoto was originally named, Fugu. Fugu (pronounced foo goo) is Japanese for pufferfish and I thought that was an interesting nickname for a monk. I had already started building a backstory (crouching tiger, hidden dragon, inflated fugu). And was crying out &quot;Fugu!&quot; at my computer screen whenever I succesfully hammered someone. However, some putz decided it was pronounced &quot;fug you&quot; and was too close to &quot;f*** you&quot; and petitioned me. A GM made me change it. Bah! I re-rolled eventually, and did a search of a Japanese dictionary for things like fist, foot, etc...Fumoto came up as the &quot;foot of a mountain&quot;, which I liked. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>
