<br>
I used to totally get into the names of my characters when roleplaying. My very first ever EQ character was named Stonesong Hammerfaith (Dwarven cleric) and it was based on one of my AD&amp;D characters. But then something happened... I joined a guild called the Stormravens. This is how I looked to other players on their screens...<br>
<br>
<br>
.........Stonesong Hammerfaith &lt;Stormravens&gt;<br>
<br>
...............................0<br>
............................../T\<br>
.............................../\<br>
<br>
My name was HUGE... it took up half the screen on my monitor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      . People also hated trying to give me tells because stonesong was just soooo darn long. Everyone called me Stoney as a nick name and very shortly I wished I had just called myself Stoney. So I learned my lesson and made a shorter name for my next main, Vallis Kinsaver, A Erudite paladin. Again, my name was shortened by everyone and they just called me Val.<br>
<br>
I guess its because we type and were all a little bit lazy. So I picked a short name, Kzan for my character this time (Luckily I luv it. Seems to fit the Verant Dark Elf naming conventions too and its short enough that people really dont feel the need to abrieviate it.<br>
<br>
Silly isnt it? But thats where my name Kzan came from. I felt the need to have a short name (that was my priority) and it being one I &quot;liked&quot; was kinda of a second priority. Oh and my last name, &quot;Verto&quot; is latin for transform. I thought it fit very nice for an enchanter. Kzan Verto. And its short too!<br>
<br>
Now if only we can convince verant to change our guild name to &lt;FnF&gt; instead of &lt;Fire and Fury&gt; .....<br>
