</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 6/10/02 11:41:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upragger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pragger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/12/02 12:49:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2024.topic&index=94>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where my name came from</span><hr size=1> The story of my name...<br>
<br>
As a child in Halas, I grew up around some pretty dark folks.  The kind you always find in alleyways gambling and drinking.  I picked up a few of thier traits.  In particular I learned how to determine how much coin a person was carrying.  Yes I meant WAS carrying, because soon after I would be carrying it.  And before too long the locals quit calling me by my name given to me by my mother.  They started calling me Pragger.  It's an old thieves can't word meaning pickpocket.  The name kinda stuck.  Now I still have the name given by my mother, but I dare not speak it, although that is another story in and of itself.  Perhaps one day I shall share that tale.<br>
<br>
If you ever run across me, keep your purse well guarded and your ale shared and you won't have many problems.  O' course don't bet me about diving off some ridiculously high structure into a small pond of water.   I also grew up cliff diving.<br>
<br>
Oh and next time I catch Guard Durnix alone in Qeynos, I owe him one, he is the one responsible for my eyepatch.  Seems I was foolish in my younger years and thought that guard would not notice my hands deep within his pockets.<br>
<br>
