Calonderiel was a recurrent secondary character in the series, a loyal friend to one of the central characters. I loved the name and its sound, long and graceful as an elven name should be. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Added benefits: it's shortened to 'Cal' by friends, but was long enough to discourage random &quot;can u sow plzd00dthx&quot; tells back on Xev (though i knew too little about EQ when i picked the name originally to have chosen it with either purpose in mind!)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Fierenduil was of my own creation... wanted another long, 'typically' elven fantasy name. Ended up being something of a combined homage itself: 'Fier' (from Fier'Dal, obviously), from the game i had grown to know and love; and the 'enduil' as a LoTR-influenced ending, from my first foray into fantasy books when i was knee-high to a brownie scout.<br>
