Actually, I wanted my characters name to reflect who they were, so I really throught hard when creating my Mage's name. <br>
<br>
My character is a female, dark elven, magician; both beautiful, and evil. With the help of my boyfriend that is fluent in Spanish, I came up with Cielo Infierno, which losely translates to Heaven and Hell in Spanish (cielo can also mean sky). The first name &quot; Cielo&quot; or &quot;Heaven&quot; refers to her physical beauty, while the last name &quot; Infierno&quot; or &quot; Hell&quot; refers to her actual beliefs and behavior. The two being put together  forms an interesting contradiction <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aksej>Aksej</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/16/02 11:10:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2024.topic&index=100>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where did your name come from?</span><hr size=1> The main character I left behind on a different server is named Jeska, a Wood Elf Druidess of Tunare.  As I sat last night contemplating names for my new FV character it hit me that I wanted to be as far away from the type of play prominent on that server I reversed the letters and viola, Aksej was born.  A bit unusual, but I actually like it.<br>
The name Jeska was derived from hours of typing and retyping various combinations...sadly, most people who saw her thought my RL name was Jessica, which it is not.  Her last name of Ladanae is Drow for dark lady... her family tree holds dark elf blood.<br>
My Barbarian rogue on that server is named Hadaka D'Argel.  Hadaka is Barbaric for serpent, and argel means hidden in the Celtic tongue. <br>
Aksej is far too young to even consider a surname as yet.<br>
